                        <div class=""tab-pane fade in active"" id=""tab1"">
                            <p>
                                <i class=""rt-icon-weather-sunny""></i>
                                We are committed to help you protect our most precious resource. This is not only our motto but who we are.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                At Enviro Metsi we provide a wide variety of water and wastewater related services to help manage South Africa's precious water resources. These include the
                                management, operation and maintenance of water and wastewater plants,");
            WriteLiteral(@" process monitoring as well as plant & process assessments, training of personnel
                                involved in these processes and assistance with any of the Blue Drop / Green Drop assessment criteria.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                While we go the extra mile to serve our customers, our involvement also impacts the community at large. We prefer to make use of local suppliers as well as
                                local labour in order to uplift the local community. Where certain skills are lacking within the local community, we aim to develop these skills. This is
                                aimed at empowering the local people, ultimately enriching their lives.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                All of this is done while keeping our motto in mind: WE are committed to help YOU protect OUR most precious resource.
                            </p>
     ");
            WriteLiteral(@"                   </div>
                        <div class=""tab-pane fade"" id=""tab2"">
                            <p>
                                Enviro Metsi (Pty) Ltd has, since its founding in 1995, been dedicated to contribute towards the protection and improvement of our water resources through
                                the Operation, Maintenance and Management of Water- and Wastewater Treatment Works in both the industrial and domestic fields.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <i class=""rt-icon-earth""></i>
                                From the get-go, Enviro Metsi endeavoured to provide the most appropriate treatment solution to our clients.  This began with the process of developing
                                and optimizing the single cell protein recovery process for use on abattoir effluent in 1995 and is continuing today as we aim to make use of the most
                                effective technologies");
            WriteLiteral(@" in our operation and maintenance practices.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                Enviro Metsi has operated a wide range of water- and wastewater treatment processes for various private industries as well as governmental departments
                                all over South Africa. These plants ranged in capacity all the way up to 20 Ml/d.  Even though the processes, plant configurations and sizes varied, our
                                dedication remained the same: We are committed to help you protect our most precious resource.
                            </p>

                        </div>
                        <div class=""tab-pane fade"" id=""tab3"">
